      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The civil rights movement in the US was a pivotal moment in American history, marking a turning point in the fight for racial equality. The movement began with the Montgomery Bus Boycott (1955-1956), led by Dr. Martin Luther King Jr., after Rosa Parks' courageous act of defiance against segregation. Key milestones include the March on Washington (1963), where King delivered his iconic \"I Have a Dream\" speech, and the passage of the Civil Rights Act (1964) and Voting Rights Act (1965), which outlawed segregation and protected voting rights. The movement's momentum continued with the Selma to Montgomery Marches (1965) and the assassination of Dr. King in 1968, but it ultimately paved the way for significant progress in the fight against systemic racism.",
