      "role": "user",
      "content": "interesting. so you're saying the nonviolent way was actually better because it got policy changes? i feel like some people argue that the more militant groups actually forced the government to act faster because they were scared. do historians actually agree that nonviolence was more effective, or is that just one way of looking at it?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
